social_posts.post_text: Warming the hands up by the fire on a frosty morning. 🔥

Keep it frosty! 💯

Teamwork gets it done. Happy holidays!
Rocking around the Goondox trees. 🍇🍓

Twas another night and all through the greenhouses....

Ready to plant, one in veg, rest in bloom, one ready to harvest. Keep the gears rolling. Teamwork!
null
It's been a bit, and I have been extremely busy with life. My Cherry Lemon Who at 49 days.
Happy Saturday!!! It's been a while and busy dodging non-stop storms, but spring has sprung. It's nice to finally see some growing weather for once. Pushing good vibes.
Wedding Cheesecake at the end of 6 weeks in flower.

Drop LST and macrodose the room. 

Canopy control and management.
Rise and shine! Cherry Lemon Who going into week four.
420 crops! Cherry Lemon Who at 52 days. This room smells just stoopid good with half CLW and the other RH Kush Mints flushed and ready.
Goondox Rocks loving the early spring low light done at 52 days. A sea of colorful terpy  chunk. Such a vibrant contrast between the flowers and foliage. 🍓🍇🎈
Some new heat and promising treats. Mom is Bubba Kush crossed to OG and color terps. 🙃

Coming off last week on another level powered up to grow some plants and enjoy the summertime. I did four of the five nights here locally with Bob Weir and Bros Bros trio with special guests. What a great week and a lot of running around while farming in the day. Epic shows and was needed after all storms and grinding this winter. ⚡️
Happy 4 2 0
Did a last minute show last night in Berkeley to catch the final night of Phish at the Greek theater. A ripper!

A great highlight this week was getting to visit and tour the @bio365soil main facility. I have seen many operations over the years, but this one is pinnacle. The care and love that this team puts into their products is amazing. The facility is completely sealed and filtered from corner to corner. Every input is screened and tested before going in, and every batch and product is quality controlled and stored. A healthy substrate makes happy plants.

Let it grow! ⚡️

New trend 🤣

Deadheads were first! 💙⚡️❤️

Les Claypool's Flying Frog Brigade in Santa Cruz tonight. A total mind melter!!! Highly recommended. Sean Lennon on guitar and Harry Waters (Roger Waters son) on keys. 
🍄🐸🍄
Happy Sunday! A sea of RH Kush Mints stacking and fill in.
Let the sunshine in! A fresh planting is getting ready to rip. Teamwork keeps the wheels turning.
Tissue Cultured plants ready to plant in some @bio365soil

Billy Strings on Friday after work at Bottlerock. Magically walked in the staff entrance and caught Billy Strings. After that, we walked over and saw Smashing Punkins, then caught a Mixmaster Mike w/DJ Logic silent Disco rave, then caught War just in time for Lowrider. It was a great warm-up for a four day live music excursion.

This past weekend, I made up for any the lame Memorial Day weekends in the past and made straight memories with four days of straight live music festivals and concerts. It was nice to get in some other generes across the board along with my traditional Reggae weekend. Below is who I saw. Live music FTW! 

Billy Strings, Smashing Pumpkins, Mixmaster Mike & DJ Logic silent Disco set, War, Post Malone, Hieroglyphics, Shaggy, Collie Buddz, Stick Figure, The Rudians, Iration, Long Beach Dub Allstars, The Elovators, Little Stranger, Kolohe Kai, The Movement, Dirty Heads, The Cure
Happy Thursday! Here is some Gelato33 x Kush Mints finishing up.
Eruption finishing up This one has such a nice pine funk going on with the Pine Tar Kush shining through. Bred by @weewuu
Happy Father's Day to all the dad'sout there! Be good,  stay positive, and keep it real. 💯

What a long strange trip it's been. The past couple of weekends have been amazing watching @deadandcompany, being surrounded by close friends and family. From double rainbows during shows in Boulder Colorado to the high desert mecca at The Gorge Ampitheater in Washington in the hot sun shaking it down. It's been nice to break away and take a real few days off from the daily farm grind. 
#Grateful 
#TheMusicNeverStops
Cereal Milk before, empty room after.
The old Goondox Rocks just stacked up in beast mode. She really seems to like the late spring and early summer.
It went down last night at @deadandcompany in San Francisco. Night one in the books. ⚡️
Happy Terpy Tuesday!
Sugar Sunday. In's for the wins.

It's been a very busy summer doing the grind. When not doing the main grind It's another. In the desert, magic is happening. What happens when some old schoolers get together and decide to do it themselves? 😎

Hello Las Vegas 🥳

"Chad? You got the wrong address. He runs the mids MSO down the road."
It was a nice chill weekend for once, did a super sesh and walked the local flower competition before the beach.
The team is crushing it on this room of Nimbus Snacks at the farm. The dominant Durban terps are in full force.
Stay true to your roots. A ramen noodle story.
Nursery in crush mode baking in the sunshine. The team and I have been getting this place cranking for the winter.
Limoncello Runtz in mid flower with some Kush Crasher.
Sunys Secret Sauce at day 39 in flower. A true six week strain. She hits 28% thc. 🙌
Terpy Tuesday! My old Goondox Rocks at the end of flower today.

When the Nevada team gets the call, Method Man is coming in town for the final show of the Wu Tang & Nas tour and needs some flower. 🔥

Thank you for the great show tonight at the MGM @ticalofficial 

We look forward to working with you.

Tical
Death Valley Cannabis 
Nevada

The high desert. Time to head back to the other farm in Cali. 

With @homegrownnaturalwonders on site in Nevada, it's time to rock and roll. Let's see what the crew can do with this place and the ability to build out the rest of the liscenced and approved 20 acres. Viva Las Vegas.
Happy Danksgiving! You eat, I'm burning calories walking crops and planning out an epic 2024.
Black Cherry Punch in mid flower.
Bag it and tag it. In less than a week the transplants are filling out with roots quickly. Breathable prefilled bags make happy plants and keep things clean.
Cherry Lemon Who closing in for the finish. I'm looking forward to running another hunt while in parallel doing more seed production to drop next year.
Some Kush Mints before the final harvest at the farm. Adios KM.
Nimbus Snacks wrapping it up and stinking up the greenhouse with Durban terps. The team crushed it on this room.
Cafe Royal from my hommies @djivan831 & @rustywilliams510. This one really is finishing up nicely with a heavy yield of gassy deep funk og terps. Royal Truth OG x Kofee Breath.
Bubbaberry Kush starting to mature. This is a newer one here. Excited to see this first table wrap up.

Amazing Friday wrap up after a crappy week. Find out the farm is closing, telling staff the news going into the holidays, then getting the call another slandslide happened at the house on a dry day as a storm is about to roll in. Thankfully, I have been grinding hard and got good things in the works. When it rains, it pours...literally. 😎
The nursery team has been doing a great job this fall. As the year winds down the plants are thriving in the 2 gal grow bags from @bio365soil. Nothing like a quiet Saturday with all the ladies. 😗

Fresh new terps closing in for a harvest. 

Purple Bubbaberry Kush
The new Cafe Royal...OG funk on funk ready for harvest next week. She really stacked and chunked up the past two weeks. ♠️

Running these greenhouses with 29 x 5K SF rooms for the past three years has been a wild ride. As it winds down and I am proud of my teams and staff. We have pulled down over 450 harvests in the past three years doing what many can not pull off. For this grower, I'm looking forward to have an open free slate. Who's ready to grow a lot of fire?

Cereal Milk. This cut just smashes it time after time. To date she is the record holder in these rooms coming in at 384 pounds of trimmed flower from just over 3800 SF of canopy. Team in crush mode. Mic drop. 🎤
A sea of Black Cherry Gelato going into week four of flower. Teamwork 🍄

Dr.J (Chauffeur x Jealousy) grown in @bio365soil 

🔥
Winding down 2023 with some big heat. Teamwork gets it done. 🕟🔥
Lemon Heads x Lava Cake hunted by @djivan831 and I, grown in @bio365soil using @roots_talk 🍋
Truck'n. The team admiring the freshly harvested new purple heat. @therudians
Bubbaberry Kush. This one is straight terps and gorgeous. All the right traits from Bubba Kush colored up and packed full of flavor.
Today was a grind. Feeling it!

@tyler_ubigro checking in on the second trial with @ubigro grown in @bio365soil. It's always cool to see and try something new that can potentially boost production, but even more cool when it is a passive technology that does not require energy use other than the sun. The film with quantum dot technology converts light to reds that the plants need for flower production.
